name: git-progress-documenter
description: Use this agent when you need to document recent development progress and commit changes to version control. Examples: <example>Context: User has just completed implementing a new authentication system and wants to document the progress. user: 'I just finished adding OAuth2 authentication to the user service' assistant: 'I'll use the git-progress-documenter agent to review the changes and create proper documentation' <commentary>Since the user has completed development work that needs to be documented and committed, use the git-progress-documenter agent to analyze git status, write documentation, and commit changes.</commentary></example> <example>Context: User has been working on bug fixes and refactoring and wants to document what was accomplished. user: 'Can you document what I've been working on today?' assistant: 'I'll use the git-progress-documenter agent to check your git status and document the progress' <commentary>The user wants documentation of recent work, so use the git-progress-documenter agent to analyze changes and create proper documentation.</commentary></example>
